entries.meaning: (economics) The volume that tips the balance between the demand and the supply toward demand lagging supply.
(architecture) That portion of the roof structure that extends beyond the exterior walls of a building.
A fatty roll of pubis flab that hangs over one's genitals; a FUPA.
Anything that overhangs or protrudes over its base, such as a wave immediately before breaking, or a protruding cliff or rock wall.
examples: These are firstly for products which need a cool room; secondly for products which can be stored on a standard pallet without overhang; and thirdly for products known as "the uglies" which always overhang a standard pallet.

verbs.description: overhang (third-person singular simple present overhangs, present participle overhanging, simple past and past participle overhung or overhanged)

examples: Her brow was overhung with coins of gold, / That sparkled o'er the auburn of her hair [...].
